#page-title{
display:none;
}
a{

}
.article{
display:flex;
flex-direction:row;
width:100%;
border-bottom:1px solid rgb(229, 229, 229);
padding-bottom:30px;
}
.picture{
flex:1 1 0%;
margin-right:19px;
max-width:300px;
}
.words{
flex:1 1 0%;
width:100%;
}
.heading{
font-family:"roboto condensed";
font-size:14px;
font-weight:bold;
color:#800080;
cursor:pointer;
}
.heading:hover{
color:black;
}
.heading2{
font-family:"roboto condensed";
font-size:14px;
font-weight:bold;
color:rgb(102, 102, 102);
cursor:pointer;
margin-bottom:8px;
height:18px;
display:none;
}
.coolheading{
font-family:"playfair display";
font-size:22px;
font-weight:bold;
line-height:1.4;
color:black;
cursor:pointer;
}
.coolheading:hover{
color:#800080;
text-decoration:underline;
}
.normalcy{
font-family:"noto serif";
font-size:17px;
line-height:1.7;
}
.giant{
font-family:"rammetto one";
}
@media only screen and (max-width:600px){
.article{
flex-direction:column;
min-height:150px;
}
.picture{
width:100%;
max-width:100%;
}
.heading{
display:none;
}
.heading2{
display:initial;
}

[[span class="normalcy"]]GERMANY—According to brand new SCPPER data collected from the past twenty four hours, this article gained a Kalinillion upvotes by virtue of being a decently formatted, mildly funny article. The Wilson's Score is 100%, higher than WDB, TINAD, and SCP-173, and has been translated by both CN branches. It appears that this astronomical growth will never end, and will continue to get to the author's head in perpetuity. Unfortunately, we have not been able to get a word with the author, although we did get some exclusive new information. They state that they are unable to properly expand on this article in a meaningful way. They were last seen approaching a McDonald's.[[/span]]
